An Act relative to civic test requirements for graduation.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 2 of Chapter 71 of the General Laws, as appearing in chapter 296 of the Acts of
2 2018, is hereby amended by inserting at the end thereof the following:-
3 “(e) All public high schools shall provide a civics test for all of their students prior to
4 graduation. Beginning in the 2021-2022 school year, in order to graduate from high school or
5 obtain a general equivalency diploma, a pupil must correctly answer at least 60 of the 100
6 questions listed on a civics test that is identical to the civics portion of the naturalization test used
7 by the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services. A pupil who does not obtain a
8 passing score on the test that is identical to the civics portion of the naturalization test may retake
9 the test until the pupil obtains a passing score. Pupils who receive special education shall not be
10 required to achieve passing scores on the civics test in order to graduate from high school.
